INSTALL - Project N2
====================

Prerequisites
-------------

  - bash 4.x or later
  - git

Installation
------------

Clone the repository and run the installer:

    cd "$HOME"
    git clone git@github.com:hengyang-zhao/n2.git .n2
    .n2/install.sh

The installer appends entrance snippets to existing dot-files (~/.bashrc,
~/.bash_profile, ~/.vimrc, ~/.tmux.conf, ~/.gitconfig).  It does not
overwrite, backup, or soft-link your original files.

The cloned directory can be named and placed arbitrarily.  M2 directories,
however, must follow the naming convention documented in n2(7).

Environment Variables
---------------------

  AUTO_CONFIRM=yes    Automatically confirms all installation prompts.
  PLAYGROUND=yes      Installs to a temporary directory instead of $HOME.

Example:

    AUTO_CONFIRM=yes .n2/install.sh

Uninstallation
--------------

Run uninstall.sh to see the list of modified files:

    .n2/uninstall.sh

Then manually edit each listed file to remove the code blocks between
the "=== N2 ENTRANCE BEGIN ===" and "=== N2 ENTRANCE END ===" markers.

After removing those blocks, you may delete the N2 directory itself.
